{
  "name": "RPlog_The_Third_Battle_of_Coruscant_Part_II",
  "title": "The Republic Falls in the Throne Room",
  "summary": "The savage duel between the wanderer Simon and the Sith huntress Kacela rages up the Palace steps and crashes into the former Emperor's Throne Room, where the dying New Republic President Woren Isaal and a roomful of trapped senators await the Empire's victory. As Vice Admiral Airion Cimber enters in triumph and pronounces the death of the Republic to the defiant Isaal, Simon -- wounded and slipping -- spots his young charge Mira hiding beneath the throne and chooses to surrender rather than abandon her, extinguishing his lightstaff even as Kacela, lost in animal rage and obeying Valak's order to take him alive, slashes him to his knees. Mira hurls her favorite stones at the Hunter and is struck down and hurled into the wall for it. With the prisoners secured by officers Kizuka, Devron, Zeak, and Hawke, Cimber orders Simon and Mira sent to the Emperor aboard the Palpatine, has Simon safely sedated, and ascends the stairs as the captured senator Ginger screams 'Long live the Republic!' -- to which Cimber coolly replies that the New Republic is dead, while Zeak prepares to raise the Imperial Ensign over the reclaimed capital.",
